HEADWORD: Ant thrush
<hw>Ant" thrush`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>One of several species of tropical birds, of the Old World, of the
genus <gen>Pitta</gen>, somewhat resembling the thrushes, and feeding
chiefly on ants.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>See <cref>Ant bird</cref>,
under <er>Ant</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

